AB  - This paper develops a model of an economy that uses two exchange markets: an official market in which the exchange rate is determined by central bank intervention, and a free market in which the exchange rate is determined by market forces. The official market handles selected imports and exports, while the free market handles the remaining imports and exports, and capital transactions. The model is used to discuss the effects of various policies on the differential between the free and the official exchange rates and on the balance of payments.
